3 Hours Ago They were said to have exchanged gunfire with the victim's security detail before whisking him away. Spokesperson for the police in the state, ASP Ramhan Nansel, confirmed the incident to SaharaReporters. He said, “Yes, he is dead, his corpse has been removed and taken to the morgue for post mortem examination and investigation has began to unravel the cause of the incident.”